<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/599> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #599" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 6.42.3; Fast. Cap. ([- -C]ossus II; [- -M]aluginens. II; [- -M]acerinus; and the rest entire); Chr. 354 (Cosso II et Grasso); Degrassi 32f., 104, 398f. On Valerius, see Münzer, Gent. Val. 37, no. 7." ;
	dprr:hasID 599 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/595> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #595" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 6.39.1; Fast. Cap. ([- -Ca]pitolinus, seditionis sedandae et rei gerendae causa); Dio fr. 29; Degrassi 32f., 103f., 398f. Favorable to plebeian demands, he appointed the first plebeian Master of Horse (Liv. 6.39.3-4; Plut. Cam. 39.5; Dio fr. 29.5)." ;
	dprr:hasID 595 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/570> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #570" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 6.30.2; Diod. 15.51.1; Chr. 354 (Capitolino et Albino); Degrassi 102, 394f. The two Manlii suffered a reverse at the hands of the Volscians (Liv. 6.30.2-8)." ;
	dprr:hasID 570 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/569> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #569" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/4> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Livy lists six but Diod. eight Military Tribunes in this year, the last two in the above list being attested by Diod. alone. The name of P. Manlius is given{107} in full in Fast. Cap. on 367; {Gr} in Diod. L. Iulius is probably the Mil. Tr. of 388, but bears in Diod. the praenomen {Gr} while Sextilius appears as {Gr} or {Gr}; and M. Albinius as {Gr}; cf. Albino in Chr. 354. Of the two additional names {Gr} closely resembles the well known name Trebonius, and Erenucius ({Gr}), which is not otherwise attested, should probably be emended to Genucius or Minucius." ;
	dprr:hasID 569 .
